    title: "2. License Scope",
    paragraphs: [
      "These Terms apply to official VivyShot binaries distributed through Apple's App Store or other official channels operated by Vivy Technologies Co., Limited.",
      "Source code published in the repository is licensed separately under the licenses described in the repository and related legal files."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "3. Permitted Use",
    paragraphs: [
      "You may use VivyShot for personal or commercial work, subject to these Terms and any platform-specific store terms that apply to your copy of the App."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "4. Restrictions",
    list: [
      "Do not use the App for unlawful activity",
      "Do not remove proprietary notices included with official binary distributions",
      "Do not misrepresent unofficial builds as official VivyShot releases",
      "Do not attempt to interfere with the App, its distribution, or related services in a way that harms users or infrastructure"
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "5. Captured Content",
    paragraphs: [
      "You are responsible for the content you capture, edit, export, and share through VivyShot.",
      "That includes ensuring you have the right to capture screens, recordings, windows, documents, or communications and the right to distribute any resulting output."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "6. App Store and Platform Terms",
    paragraphs: [
      "If you obtain VivyShot through Apple's App Store, Apple may apply additional terms, billing rules, and usage conditions to that distribution.",
      "App Store purchases, refunds, and account management are handled through Apple's systems unless explicitly stated otherwise."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "7. Disclaimer",
    paragraphs: [
      'THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW.'
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "8. Limitation of Liability",
    paragraphs: [
      "TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, VIVY TECHNOLOGIES CO., LIMITED WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE APP."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "9. Governing Law",
    paragraphs: [
      "These Terms are governed by the laws of Hong Kong SAR, without regard to conflict of law principles."
    ]
  },
  {
    title: "10. Contact",
    paragraphs: [
      `Questions about these Terms can be sent to ${site.email}.`
    ]
  }
];
---

<LegalPage
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of use for VivyShot."
  updatedLabel="Last updated: March 20, 2026"
  intro="This version is intentionally simple and aligned with the repo's current licensing and distribution model. It avoids inventing pricing, tiers, or cloud features that are not finalized."
  sections={sections}
/>
